          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a kind of manual or handbook to be used by priests or senior family members, which outlines the rules and regulations (Hindu law) for performing rites of veneration to a specific class of deceased ancestors, typically the third generation back.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Nāndīśrāddhasaṃkalpa</title>
              <title type="vernacular">नान्दीश्राद्धसंकल्प</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>scribe</resp>
                <persName type="authority">Nārāyaṇa ( son of Nīlakaṇṭha)</persName>
              </respStmt>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti nāṃdīśrāddhasaṃkalpyaḥ // likhitam idaṃ kāśyāṃnīlakaṃṭhasūnunānārāyaṇena // śrī // śrī // karakṛtam aparādhaṃ kṣantum arhaṃti saṃtaḥ // (f. 9v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
